duck: Orbital period - The orbital period is the time taken for a given object to make one complete orbit about another object.
Atomic orbital - An atomic orbital is a mathematical function that describes the wave-like behavior of either one electron or a pair of electrons in an atom.
Orbital (band), a UK electronic dance music band
orbital definition: a mathematically described region around a nucleus in an atom or molecule that may contain zero, one, or two electrons.
